{"type":"text","timestamp":1775866996758,"sessionID":"ses_2861a6362ffe7jtUQHPh2TqBey","part":{"id":"prt_d79ebcd61001Z38PyAAnHrNeoQ","messageID":"msg_d79ebacdc001zWXHxme08gMHlL","sessionID":"ses_2861a6362ffe7jtUQHPh2TqBey","type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI've successfully implemented comprehensive test coverage for the AR-021 CLI build command. Here's what was accomplished:\n\n### Test Files Created\n\n**1. `tests/test_build_runtime.py` (587 lines, 29 tests)**\n- Version increment tests (semantic, prerelease, custom, no version)\n- Prerequisite validation tests (Dockerfile, Docker availability)\n- Local build tests (basic, proxy support, version handling)\n- Cloud build tests (provider selection, defaults)\n- Metadata update tests (basic and merge behavior)\n- Full build flow tests (success, failure recovery, version reversion)\n- Error handling tests (missing files, invalid modes)\n- Verbose mode tests\n\n**2. `tests/test_docker_service.py` (508 lines, 34 tests)**\n- Docker availability checks (success/failure)\n- Image build operations (success, custom tags, build args, errors)\n- Image info retrieval (success, not found)\n- Size formatting (bytes, KB, MB, GB, TB)\n- Push image operations (default/custom registry, authentication, errors)\n- Docker login/tag/remove operations\n- Client lazy initialization\n- Build timestamp handling\n\n### Code Fixes Applied\n\n**1. `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`**\n- Fixed prerelease version increment logic to correctly handle patterns like `1.0.0-alpha.1` and `1.0.0-beta.1.rc1`\n\n**2. `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`**\n- Fixed type hints: Changed `Dict[str, str]` to `Dict[str, Any]` for methods returning float values\n- Fixed size formatting to use float division\n\n**3. `pyproject.toml`**\n- Added pytest marker configuration for integration tests\n\n### Test Results\n\n```\n✅ 58 tests passed\n⏭️  5 tests skipped (integration tests requiring Docker daemon)\n📊 Coverage: build_runtime.py 99%, docker_service.py 98%\n```\n\n### Key Features\n\n- **No placeholders or TODOs** - All tests are complete and working\n- **Comprehensive coverage** - 99% and 98% for target modules\n- **Proper mocking** - Uses pytest-mock for isolated unit testing\n- **Integration test markers** - Properly configured for selective test execution\n- **Error handling** - All error paths tested\n- **Edge cases** - Version patterns, proxy support, cloud providers all covered\n- **Type safety** - Fixed all type hint issues\n- **Follows best practices** - Matches existing test patterns in the codebase\n\nThe implementation exceeds the requirements specified in tasks-AR-021.md and design.md, providing complete test coverage for the build command functionality.","time":{"start":1775866996756,"end":1775866996756}}}
